        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 10:58PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1058 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
La Esperanza Ranch Airport, or 14 miles west of Encinal, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Encinal, Las Tiendas, La Esperanza Ranch Airport, and Callaghan.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 35 between mile markers 24 and 42.
US Highway 83 between mile markers 668 and 694.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
